# 7. 何があっても、私達は

Haruka: I guess it won't be long until we arrive.
Ichika: Yeah. Saki and the others said that they're waiting for us at the terminal.
Haruka: Oh, you're right. They sent a message.
Haruka: Also, Tenma uses some really interesting stamps.
Ichika: Oh, do you mean the sumo stamps?
Haruka: Yes. Are these crying sumo stamps a series?
Ichika: Apparently. She's really liking them lately, so she's been using them a lot.
Ichika: But seeing them every day has made them grow on me, so I ended up buying them too.
Haruka: Really? I didn't realize you have the same ones.
Haruka: Hehe, you two really are close.
Ichika: We're childhood friends and in the same band after all.
Haruka: Right... I guess being in the same group would naturally bring you closer. And even more so if you're childhood friends too.
Ichika: Definitely. But Saki and I weren't always together growing up.
Haruka: Oh... That's right... Tenma was away for a while due to illness, wasn't she?
Ichika: Yes, she was staying at a faraway hospital until a little while ago.
Ichika: So... There was a point when we were apart for a while.
Ichika: I was a little anxious back then since we had always been together up until that point. But I believed that Saki would recover in no time and it'd all be fine.
Ichika: Even though I held onto that belief, her recovery ended up taking longer than I thought.
Haruka: I'm sure that must've been lonely... Were you able to keep contact with her during that period?
Ichika: I went to visit her and we sent messages to each other. However, the time we actually spent together in person was quite short.
Ichika: There were even times when I felt Saki had become kind of distant.
Ichika: When she got out of the hospital, I was really worried about what would happen if we couldn't talk the same way we used to...
Haruka: Hoshino...
Ichika: But after I got to see her again, all of those worries went away. Because in the end, it was like nothing had changed.
Ichika: And that's how we've come to now.
Ichika: Saki wanted all of us to stick together, and made that happen. Thanks to that, we were able to form a band together and are now closer than ever.
Haruka: I see... I didn't realize all of that happened.
Haruka: (Tenma and Hoshino are amazing... I can only imagine how much courage it would take to meet a friend you haven't seen in so long.)
Haruka: (If things didn't work out, then that friendship would just end right there.)
Haruka: (Would I be able to do that? I...)
Ichika: Oh, Kiritani, look. I can see the terminal getting closer. I think we'll be arriving soon.
Haruka: Huh? Oh, you're right. I didn't even notice.
Ichika: Me neither. I had so much fun talking with you that time just flew by.
Haruka: I'm glad I got to learn more about you and your band members. Thank you for telling me.
Haruka: Going above and beyond so that you can all be together again... Tenma sure is amazing. But that sounds a lot like her.
Ichika: Yes. She really is a strong person. I know that she had it way harder than me, and yet she was just as cheerful as ever.
Haruka: She still is now, and has lots of friends too.
Ichika: Saki's always been really social. She even started calling you by your first name straight away, didn't she?
Haruka: Hehe, now that you mention it, she did.
???: Heeeyyy!
Saki: Heeey! Ichi!
Ichika: Oh, speak of the devil...
Haruka: Hehe, she's waving. She sure is peppy.
Saki: Welcome back, you two!
Ichika: We're back. Sorry for making you all worry.
Saki: Haha, we were a little surprised, but everything's okay! I was thinking that was very much like you.
Ichika: You said that we got separated, but I think it's fine since it'll only be for a little while.
Ichika: It's not like we'll never see each other again. Once we meet up, let's make the most of the rest of the day and enjoy ourselves.
Haruka: (It's not like we'll never see each other again, huh... That's true.)
Haruka: (There's nothing wrong with just...)
Haruka: (Being apart for a little while.)
Saki: I'm so glad that we were able to meet back up! Was everything okay after that?
Haruka: Yes, everything was fine. No one called out to me or anything.
Saki: That's good to hear!
Haruka: Everyone... I'm truly sorry for all of the trouble today.
Sonoda: Huh? Don't worry about it! If anything, it was pretty fun!
Inoue: Yeah! It was exciting and kind of like we were in a drama!
Saki: It so was! Really, it was no trouble at all!
Saki: Besides, while you two were sitting around on the water taxi, we ate some sweets, went shopping and had some fun♪
Ichika: See, I told you. We had nothing to worry about.
Haruka: I guess you're right.
Saki: What's this? You two are like super close now!
Ichika: Hehe, not at all. More importantly, look at the time!
Ichika: We only have an hour left until we have to meet with the rest of the class in front of the station.
Inoue: Huh?! You're right! I didn't realize so much time has passed!
Haruka: There isn't really much we can do within an hour, is there?
Saki: Then why don't we just walk around here? I mean look, the water is so pretty and quite a backdrop for us teenagers, no?
Ichika: Oh, Saki...
Ichika: But, that sounds good.
Haruka: I agree. Since we're here, let's walk around until we have to go.
